Michael Rule <manikmike(-at-)gmail.com> wrote:
>What did you volks do for the overall prep of the fiberglass?

Prep: 20 years of neglect, a power wash and finally a light sanding.

Paint: Nautical gel coat resin applied with brush and roller.  White.
The second (final) coat included some resin hardener to the mix.

